A deadly explosion killed at least 35, and wounded as many as 70 people in the
Moscow airport Domodedovo. Early reports
[assert](http://echo.msk.ru/news/744323-echo.html) (ru) that the attack was a
suicide bomb. Information has been coming in from many sources. Twitter is
experiencing an explosion of tweets with the hashtag
[#Domodedovo](http://twitter.com/#%21/search?q=%23domodedovo). At the moment
the information flow is extremely intense; the hashtag is receiving about 100
message per second. LiveJournal has been less mobile in reflecting the news
not to speak of TV channels that were at least half an hour late with covering
the disaster.

**Initial reporting**

The first news came from Twitter-user Ilya Likhtenfeld
([@likhtenfeld](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld)). Below is the selection of
his tweets:

> [16:44](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29534965221826561): В
> домодедово теракт! Страшный взрыв в здании аэропорта! Десятки тел разорваных
> людей! Звоните близким. RT

There’s a terrorist act in Domodedovo! An enormous explosion in the building
of the airport! Dozens of broken bodies! Call your relatives. RT

> [16:48](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29535980989976577)
> @[emenschikova](http://twitter.com/emenschikova) у меня там бизнес, много
> сотрудников

I have business there, there are many employees of mine

> [16:57](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29539033403101185) По
> оценкам моих сотрудников около 70 погибших! Сергей вынес 15 человек раненых!

According to my employees there are more than 70 dead! Sergey carried out 15
wounded!

> [17:14](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29542559910985728) У людей
> находящихся рядом с Домодедово начинаются перебои с сотовой связью.

People in Domodedovo are having problems with cellphone connection

> [17:16](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29542991580368896) Сейчас в
> новостных лентах ничинают занижать кол-во погибших

Now, all the newswires are starting to lower number of casualties.

> [17:28](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29546164890116096) Не можем
> найти сотрудницу, которая была на смене. Нигде её нет

We can’t find our employee who was on the shift. Can’t find her anywhere.

> [17:34](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29547692182999040) Всем
> отвечаю: у меня там более 100 сотрудников работают! Вся инфа от них! Фото и
> видео скоро будут!

I’m replying to everyone – I have more than 100 employees there! All the
information is from them! Photos and videos will appear shortly!

> [17:48](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29551165834264577) НАЧАЛИ
> ГЛУШИТЬ СОТОВУЮ СВЯЗЬ! постоянные перебои в разговорах с людьми, которые там
> находятся

THEY STARTED TO STIFLE THE MOBILE CONNECTION! Constant breaks during phone
conversations with the people that are there.

> [17:54](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29552564454297601) Уже
> двоих сотрудников не можем найти. Ещё одну девочку увозят на скорой

We can’t find two persons from our staff. One girl is on the ambulance

> [17:56](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29553098397589504) Погибших
> не менее 70! Это говорят несколько человек, который были прямо там. Раненых
> много больше 100

Number of casualties is not less than 70! This is being said by several people
who have been there. There are more than 100 wounded.

> [17:56](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29553208519041025) Всё
> оцепили никого не пускают.

Now they (police – GV) have surrounded everything. They’re not letting anyone
(in or out – GV)

> [18:07](http://twitter.com/#!/likhtenfeld/status/29555807917969409) Это не
> багаж! Бомба была на человеке, который стоял среди встречающих. Рядом с
> Азия-кафе.

It wasn't luggage! Bomb was on a person who was standing among those who were
meeting people. Next to Asia-cafe.

